Sentencas: Fabrication of microporous structures for the anode of a thin film solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC(s)) using controlled etching process has led us to increased power density and increased cell robustness.
Titulo: Triple-phase boundary and power density enhancement in thin solid oxide fuel cells by controlled etching of the nickel anode

Sentencas: Micropores were etched in the nickel anode by both wet and electrochemical etching processes.
Titulo: Triple-phase boundary and power density enhancement in thin solid oxide fuel cells by controlled etching of the nickel anode

Sentencas: The samples etched electrochemically showed incomplete etching of the nickel leaving linked nickel islands inside the pores.
Titulo: Triple-phase boundary and power density enhancement in thin solid oxide fuel cells by controlled etching of the nickel anode

Sentencas: Samples which were wet- etched showed clean pores with no nickel island residues.
Titulo: Triple-phase boundary and power density enhancement in thin solid oxide fuel cells by controlled etching of the nickel anode

Sentencas: Moreover, the sample with linked nickel islands in the anode pores showed higher output power density as compared to the sample with clean pores.
Titulo: Triple-phase boundary and power density enhancement in thin solid oxide fuel cells by controlled etching of the nickel anode

Sentencas: This enhancement is related to the enlargement of the surface of contact between the fuel-anode-electrolyte (the triple-phase boundary).
Titulo: Triple-phase boundary and power density enhancement in thin solid oxide fuel cells by controlled etching of the nickel anode
